rComments: Two weeks into this class with dr. Mileva and she's just amazing. Her lectures are very easy-going and entertaining. I would love to have her again for future classes.

Prof. Mileva was a fantastic teacher, and I'm glad to have taken this class with her! She did her best to make the most of online learning, and was very accommodating. Her lectures were asynchronous which can be tricky to keep on top of, but the content was very clear and interesting, which made the whole experience much better!

I like Professor Mileva. She is very passionate about the subject she is teaching. 2021W might have been a bit of missed opportunity here as the class took to online format and I think she is a professor that will do better in in-person lectures.

Seems like a nice prof, but lectures often felt super heavy with lots of details. Although references to her own experiences and personal anecdotes may have helped some students understand concepts, I found it generally made lectures drag on significantly longer than required. Grading seemed fair and prof was easy to access, so some positives here.

I love Prof Mileva. Her class was overall super accessible and organized considering it was asynchronous. The class was so engaging and interesting b/c she has a young son and she would relate the course content to her real life experiences, making it easier to remember things. Overall, the best uni course I've taken.

This class is evaluated by 4 quizzes and 1 final which are really easy by just reading the textbook. She is a nice and caring prof but she jumps over topics a lot which causes me headache by trying to understand the topics covered in class. But it is really easy to get A+ since she quizzes based on the textbook.

prof mileva is hands down one of the best at uOttawa. she is incredible at teaching and conveying the material in a simple and easy to understand manner. she is the kindest soul i have ever met! she includes lots of life lessons which are inspiring and kind :) u need to study and show up to class to pass her exams (they are super easy if u do!)

Dr. Mileva was the sweetest prof- she genuinely cared about us and how we were doing. Despite being online, she tried her best to make the synchronous lectures as engaging as possible, and it made everything so much better. The quizzes and exam were super easy; pay attention in class and do the TopHat readings and you'll be good to go!
Very passive aggressive and won't give extra time of assignment! I could say a lot about her but she was nice enough so if you don't have to speak to her personally you will be fine.

I don't understand why her rating is so high, she spends the majority of her class time talking about her own mental health or just random off topic things. Her slides provide like no information and she gives no extra credit or any form of study materials. basically like going in blind when you write her exam
Dr Mileva is very kind, helpful, and understanding. Her lectures are very clear and she tries to explain concepts in multiple ways to ensure understanding.
I loved prof mileva! She was genuinely on of the best profs i had this semester. Reading was just tiring for me;

She doesn't really know the material all that well - she has to look up stuff each time you ask her a question. Her lectures aren't necessary - the textbook is what is tested, she just does the videos to clarify more difficult concepts. However, I think her videos are interesting and worth watching. She makes it seem like she doesn't want questions
very caring and easy to understand prof. Her videos were a bit long but she explained stuff really well and answered questions and concerns in a timely manner.

Super kind and bright! She emphasizes all the most important concepts to know and quiz/exam questions are mostly examples (application questions) so make sure you understand all the concepts and their differences. All tests are based off of the textbook so taking a few notes while you read through might not be a bad idea

Dr. Mileva genuinely cares about her students. Course material was easy to understand and her lectures were concise, clear, and very engaging. Tests are well spread out, and she went above and beyond to ensure her students understood all of the material necessary for tests. Highly recommend!
Best professor ever, her videos are so helpful and she is very caring and nice.

Mlieva is an all around great professor. She really wants you to succeed. Be prepared to do a lot of textbook reading. The tests are based off the textbooks. The only thing I didn't like is that the lectures didn't always reflect exactly what was on the quiz. Sometimes, even different terms were interchanged, making it a little confusing.

nice prof, a bit annoying especially when she allows her child to mess around in her lectures. wanted us to do well but used too many platforms at once. not my favorite prof but definitely not the worst! teaches as if you are an elementary student. lectures werent necessary, uses tophat that teaches for her basically
AMAZING professor! She is super kind and kept the lectures very interesting by incorporating videos and examples. I would recommend to everyone to have her as a professor.

She's a very kind and down to earth person. She explained concepts well and made her lectures engaging. Definitely make sure you take thorough notes from the textbook as all assessments are based off of textbook material. I really enjoyed her class.

Dr. Mileva is such a caring professor and an incredible lecturer. Even though her course was online, it was so engaging with live polls, and opportunities to ask questions. She is super down to earth, and I cannot recommend her enough, shes awesome.

Mileva is a GEM! The only prof I had this semester that actually gave a basic workload. Use the textbook as much as you can since the questions will be based on it. Her youtube lectures were so sweet and amazing! TAKE HER IF YOU CAN!

I loved her Youtube lecture videos since she gave many helpful examples explaining the concept. She is a very caring prof and tried her best despite this being her first time teaching this course. The course itself was purely based on the textbook, so focus on EVERY DETAIL in the textbook and you will do well in the course.

Professor Mileva is and I think will always be one of my favourite professors. She really truly cares about her students and is very available outside of class. She is clear about her grading (the quizzes and exam were all faculty based) and what is expected of us. STUDY THE TEXTBOOK, it's what the questions are based off. The lectures helpful too

Professor M is the sweetest, most down to earth teacher. The course examinations were 100% based on the textbook, so I made the decision to read on my own time and take detailed notes for studying afterwards. I stopped attending classes after the 1st quiz and still received an A+. However I did still work hard, you gotta do your readings!
She truly cares about her students! Yes, there is quite a lot of reading within the textbook online. However, she gives great examples through her lectures and will be very chill with the quizzes.

She is the best. She made great videos for the different topics we learnt in class which were super useful and we can rewatch them whenever we want to study. Super personable and was always great to answer questions if needed. She made me want to take further psychology classes. I hope I have her again in the future.
didn't find enjoyable, don't feel like I learned anything
Shes such a good prof. She gives great lectures and finds ways to make them fun. You cant go wrong with her!

Only downside was that you only needed to read the text to do good on the tests and her lectures were just extra incase you need more explanation. But she was very engaging and I really enjoyed her lectures.
She is such a good professor, I highly recommend her course for first year psych. You can easily do good in her course.

I love Dr. Mileva. She is a very kind and fair professor. She has the ability to reduce stress in students through her encouraging words. If you have the opportunity to be in her class, I strongly advise.

Prof. Mileva was thrown into the class right before it started and has done an amazing job preparing everyone for the quizzes/exam. She relates to students and cares about students mental health. The quizzes are fair and there are many different marks besides just quizzes.

She is an amazing professor, very caring and very thorough. There is lots of reading but that is more because of content. She cares deeply for students mental health and has been a breath of fresh air to have. Once you read the textbook and listen to her lectures (and amazing YouTube videos) you will be fine.

Professor Mileva was by far my favourite this semester, her online class was engaging and the quizzes are fair. Lots of opportunity for marks if you do the readings. She is a really caring professor who is concerned about her students mental health. Amazing professor, I would absolutely take her class again.

Prof Mileva was given this class (thats shes never taught before) like 2 days before the semester started and she did an AMAZING job teaching this class especially during Covid times. Knows her content very well and shes very understanding and cares about her students mental health. 10/10 would take her class again
Guergana is a great professor and she has adapted very well to the new system that we are all experiencing for the first time. She also relates to the students very well.

Mileva is one of the kindest profs Ive had during undergrad. Being a prof of psychology, she puts her students mental health first and is completely understanding of all situations. Her teaching style is engaging, and shes really got a good grasp of online learning and how to keep class interesting. Overall, shes just an amazing person.

Her lectures were interesting and I never fell asleep even though it was a 7-10pm. Her grading was clear and when we had to switch to online mid-semester because of corona she her class was definitely one of the better formatted ones, she encoured participation and was just so sweet
Pretty straightforward course. Go to class, pay attention, take notes. Course material is super interesting, and Professor Mileva makes it interesting as well! She's really sweet!
AMAZING... excellent lectures and you won't regret taking her class!!! hands down one of the best prof, so genuine and caring
she is the most genuine prof I've ever had... the best! if you have the chance take one of her class you will grow as a person and learn much more than just the material.. a real gem

She is such a caring prof. This was her first online class, she responded well to the challenge. She is very responsive to student concerns and suggestions. Her lectures are engaging with lots videos to help connect what we're learning to the real world. We had a few papers, only a few pages in length and guidlines were clear. Textbook recommended
Amazing prof, by far one of the best Ive had! Highly recommend if you take good notes and study youll do perfect! I have 0 complaints

Professor Mileva is by far one of the best profs I've had. She wants the best for all her students. The course consisted of 2 reflections, final paper, midterm and final exam. Instructions are clear and she answers all questions. The course material is interesting and she actually teaches and shows videos relevant to the course. Highly recommend!

Literally, the first prof in uni who seemed like they actually cared. I had her for an online course, and she did such a great job balancing answering questions in the class and teaching the material. She breaks up lectures with interesting videos, and actually teaches! Her assignments and exams are SOOO fair. I'll be BLESSED if I have her again.
She's super kind and cares about her students so much. Great choice!
Professor Mileva is so nice and I loved her lecture. She cares about her students and gives them a lot of opportunities to do well. We had a midterm, 2 reflections, a paper and a final :)

She's very sweet, but easily distracted which makes 7-10s extra long. Need to go to lectures if u dont buy textbook bc what she adds will be tested. Assignment rubric extremely unclear and grading kinda random bc u didn't know what to include. Exams are straightforward and class is fun since she doesn't overcomplicate things. Def take w friends :)

I love this professor! I'm taking a class with her again next semester, not because I need it but just because I like her so much. She puts some info on the slides but not enough if you want a really good grade so it's important to go to the lectures unless your only goal is to pass but it's pretty easy to get an A in this class if you just attend

She is an amazing teacher. Her lectures are interesting and fun. Make sure you take good notes since her midterm/exam are also based on what she says in class. Just study the notes from class and it should be an easy A+

Take PSY 2114 with her if you can! Her lectures are fun and she tells lots of personal stories which makes the content more interesting and easy to understand. No textbook, just take good notes and you'll do really well!

She is very nice and caring. The lectures are interesting although a bit too long for a material that can be done in shorter time. Overall it was one midterm, an assignment and final exam. Evals were clear and fair. Definitely recommend her if you want an easy A.

She's lovely and knows her content but sometimes drags on the lectures for much longer than needed. Has a hard time handling class chatter and gets very offended and distracted, but otherwise a great prof. Very sweet and likable.

Honestly the sweetest prof, super caring and really straight forwarding her teaching. Gives a lot of examples/ personal experience that makes understanding concepts easier than just memorizing! Attend class to get the extra bits of informations as the slides are not everything, but study hard and it's an easy A

Prof. Mileva is interesting and passionate about the content she teaches. Her exams are straightforward, but you'll do better if you go to class since she adds information to the slides verbally. Her content can be dull, and she talks about her son a lot, which helps the content be more relatable at times, but can also lead to unfocused lectures.

Dr. Mileva shares an example from her personal life for nearly every concept explained in class (which make things easier to understand and makes the content more interesting). She is extremely caring, approachable and open to questions/class discussion. I would 100% take another class with her.

She is such an amazing speaker. Interesting and truly an inspirational class. Usually 7-10PM are quite difficult to keep awake but she made it so fun it was truly not a concern. Mid term was a bit heavy - make sure you study ahead and come to class. The paper is interesting - against do it ahead and don't leave it to the last minute.
I took a 7-10 with her this semester, and it's been the first one i've ever actually wanted to attend, super engaging lectures, and easy tests!

1 paper (25%), 1 midterm (35%) , 1 final (40%). Fair marker and fair exams. Participation is mandatory for an A+ (test has material she only brings up in the lectures). Approachable person but also stands her ground, which is commendable. Overall a great prof!

Interesting class. Lots of ted talks & class discussions. Make sure to write down everything she says because it could all be on the exam. I would take her again, she makes things interested. She talks a lot about examples from her personal life so people can relate to her!
I loved her class so much I didnt want it to end.

Lectures were interesting, no textbook or mandatory readings. Interesting videos and documentaries shown in class. Mid-term, paper and final. Exams multiple choice/fill-in-the-blanks/short answer. Listening in class will give you all the info for the exam. Would recommend.

Great prof! If you go to class and listen to the lectures, you'll do well on the midterm. There's no textbook but the slides and lecture notes are enough to do well. Prof Mileva really cares about her students and makes the lectures interesting. She's super nice and easy to talk to, I would definitely take another class with her.

Great prof. Textbook isn't needed but her slides don't contain everything either. Her midterm is mostly multiple choice with a few short answer questions as well. A lot of her questions reflect what was discussed in lectures so be sure to go to class if you want a good grade. She also shows super interesting videos in class. Fun course overall.
I really like the way she teaches, she goes pretty slow so you can write every thing she says and then just study your notes well. I find that this is the best way for me to learn.

Super nice prof! Her slides are really well written but don't contain everything so you do have to go to class to get a higher grade. She gives two short written assignments that are basically freeby marks. Definitely don't need the textbook if you go to class and pay attention. Tests reflect the stuff she emphasizes in class, so go to class!

Amazing professor!! Clearly cares about her students and is really easy to talk to about anything. The textbook is optional so just go to class and take detailed notes and you can get an A+. She also handed out candy for a couple lectures. Definitely one of my favourite professors at uOttawa!

Slides don't contain all of the info, you will need to go to class if you want above a 70%. Don't need the textbook at all. Lectures are really straight forward, easy to follow, great prof, great discussion. Midterm and final was a bit too detail oriented in my opinion but doable.

The prof is very kind and helpful. Her lecture slides contain everything needed for the exams. The assignments are straightforward. You dont need to read the textbook if you attend class and write down everything she explains. Exams are non cumulative and she even boosted our final exam marks by 10 marks.

Easy A+ class. Shes really nice, the final is non cummalitive. there is a midterm, final, and paper that are very easy to ace as long as you memorize her slides and any extra info mentioned in class. textbook not necessary.
textbook NOT essential. Super nice prof. A lot of different stuff to get grades on. If you attend lecture and study you should do well.

This prof is very caring but cannot answer a question asked in class. She usually refers you to the textbook (that is optional to buy) or to google. She is the kind of teacher that reads from her slides and is very boring. Nice person, but not a good teacher for this class. The exam was heavily based on memorization and not on comprehension.

Textbook is a waste of money,  all you need is on the slides or said in class. Any questions asked, she was usually not able to answer. She'd either write them down and google them on break or someone else in the class would answer. She's very sweet/caring! But not experienced enough in the field to teach this course, so it was kind of a let down.

Didn't really like this class. A lot of the material echoed the stuff I'd seen in my other psych classes. Assignments were time-consuming, even though they were supposed to be "grade boosters". Wouldn't really recommend unless you had a conflict like I did. Otherwise, you can expect to get the grade you want if you put in the effort...
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things', 'Tough grader']

rComments: This class is a horribly boring, expensive audiobook. The absolute most useless information I have ever received in undergrad and I have taken some bird classes. Prof is unhelpful and repeats the same basic concepts so often as to make five slides last an hour. You won't fail, but you'll wish you had taken something, anything else.

Kindest professor I've had. Incorporates anecdotes from students to enrich her lectures and have people participate. Textbook is used for background knowledge but the slides are what she focusses on when testing. 2 small assignments, a midterm and a final. Consist of MC and short answer. Know her slides and you'll get a good grade!

She's so great! Her lectures are always engaging, interesting, and make you want to participate. Only downside is that her midterms and assignment grading is SUPER specific so pay attention to what she focuses on in the lectures and don't stray AT ALL from rubric criteria for the assignments.
I loved her! She is clear on anything you want to know for the exam, she answers everyone's questions in class. She tries to make everyone participate, and gives candy if you do :) She is so cute!!

Very engaging professor. Conveys course material well. Exams are mostly based off of lecture material, however textbook chapters are good for furthering your own understanding of the material. Loved all the topics covered. Would definitely recommend this class to someone else.
Super hot prof! Very nice! Topics are interesting. Mostly tested on slideshows so textbook is not necessarily needed. MC midterms and exams can have pretty specific questions. Overall a good class.
Very nice prof, relays the information in an effective manor. Though there is a lot of content in the class and midterms are very specific. There are two assignments which are great grade boasters.

Drop the class right now if you want to preserve your GPA. I am a A student, so this is not the whining of someone that isn't willing to put in the effort for a grade. This prof is very nice, but a ridiculously hard marker with pretty unfair and super specific midterms. AVOID.

Overall really nice and easy going. A lot of her slides are word for word from the textbook but I recommend going to class for repetition sake (midterms (2) and final are SO specific). There are 2 assignments that were fun to do and easy to get A+ on. Interesting content, a lot to memorize though. She often brought treats to class for students!
